The shooting took place during the early hours of this morning at a venue in Site B. CAPE TOWN - Six people have been shot and killed at a tavern in Khayelitsha. The shooting took place during the early hours of this morning at a venue in Site B. According to police, five people died on the scene and one at the hospital. Seven people have been injured, including a six-year-old girl. The police's Novela Potelwa sayid it's alleged that a group of men stormed the tavern and started shooting randomly. "The 72-hour action plan has been activated for the arrest of yet-to-be-identified gunmen who opened fire on a dwelling in Site B, Khayelitsha." The motive is unknown and no arrests have been made.